ETHIC HAWKS: CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL 

Classification: Strictly Confidential | Standard: Forensic Integrity Protocol 

1. PURPOSE AND SCOPE 

This protocol outlines the rigorous standards maintained by Ethic Hawks regarding the protection of sensitive data, whistleblower identities, and corporate disclosures. This policy applies to all forensic audits, council charter developments, and psychosocial risk assessments. 

2. DATA ENCRYPTION & SECURE STORAGE 

Digital Evidence: All evidence collected during a Forensic Integrity Audit is processed through end-to-end encrypted channels. 

Isolation: Documentation related to Independent Council Charters is maintained in isolated digital environments to prevent unauthorized internal or external access. 

3. WHISTLEBLOWER ANONYMITY (SECURE DESK) 

Our Secure Desk is architected to protect the identity of informants. Identity masking is applied at the point of entry. No identity is disclosed unless explicit written consent is provided by the informant or required by a court mandate. 

4. NON-DISCLOSURE ASSURANCE 

Ethic Hawks operates under strict Non-Disclosure Agreements (NDAs) by default. We do not trade, share, or disclose findings, client identities, or psychosocial risk data to any third party. 

5. PROFESSIONAL SECRECY 

Every engagement is governed by a project-specific confidentiality charter. This ensures that internal psychosocial risks or governance failures remain within the remediation cycle and are shielded from the public domain. 

